ver ask for a price check!  The other person will know that you don't know jack about the item you're trying to buy/sell.  That will give him/her the advantage when you haggle.  If you're firm with your offer, then they'll think twice about trying to scam some extra PP off ya.  How do you prevent this?  KNOW YOUR ITEMS!<br><br>3) Know where the hot items come from.  Know how hard it is to get.  How rare is the drop rate.  What kinda shit you have to go through to get it.  This is crucial information and it will help you in your haggling.<br><br>4) When your deals range in the 20+Kpp, it's easier to shave off some PP than it is if the item's worth a couple Kpp.  Example:  Fungi tunic ~35kpp.  When you're dealing with this much PP, you can try to shave off ~1.5kpp-2kpp and it won't matter much (if you're buying).  The higher the price tag, the more you can shave off, most people wouldn't bother haggling to the last PP when they know they'll be a phat PP whore after selling that CoF <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   Use this to your advantage.  A couple thousand pp saved here and there will add up.<br><br>5) Try to always get PP from a deal instead of an item.  Why? Because then you'd have to sell that other damn item!  People prefer you pay in PP anyways.  Unless you're making a good trade, then go for it.<br><br>Well that's all I can think up with, but the most important thing is: KNOW YOUR MARKET!  It is a marketing principle!  The better you know the game, the more loop holes you can make for yourself.  And lastly, nobody should feel dirty or bad when they day trade.  It's hard work on your part and think of it as a service that you provide to the dungeon crawlers.   <p><center><a href="http://www.angelfire.com/" target="_blank"><img src="http://www.angelfire.com/rpg/worldx/street/ken10.gif" border="0"></a></center><font size ="3"><center><b