ways find Wu Wear at many of the vendors (Tunare Serv).  They sell at 'bout 1/3 going rate at the EC Tunnel.  So that is another example of takin' advantage of your vendor's prices and your customer's impatience.  Bargain Huntin is the name of the game.<br><br>Esol Ancientsun&lt;Tunare&gt;<br>Monk of the Ashen Order<br>28th Degree &quot;Knuckle Up Chump&quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccccc><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub38.ezboard.com/ugedalthegnome.showPublicProfile?language=EN>GedalTheGnome</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Young Grasshoppah</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(10/26/01 10:24:30 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=565.topic&index=19>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Advanced trading.</span><hr size=1> Just some more ideas on how to get a good deal and get started with trading and some things I have seen on my server =)<br><br>If your going to have an alt do the trading make it a woman. For some reason or other it seems people have a soft spot for the girls and will often give them better deals etc. Personally I always assume that the person is male at the keyboard but I still catch myself giving free pp and items to newbie wood elf women ;)<br><br>As mentioned before PATIENCE is likely the most important skill. Don't rush it just take your time and get the price you want.<br><br>If you come across a new item and you want to figure out roughly what its worth there are a few things to consider. One how difficult was it going to obtain? if it comes from Crushbone your not going to get 10k for it.<br>Secondly Who can use it? Good example is that nice staff, its a 32 dam 36 del 2hb but its ranger only. Personally I have yet to meet a ranger with 2hb over skill 4 and most of them just want to duel weild. This item should be worth  about 8-10k when you compare it to some of the other nice weapons out there but goes for about 1-2k on Xev since it is not sought after. The larger your market the better. Singing steel stuff often goes for alot less then actual value of the item simply because there aren't that many bards out there.<br><br>A nice way to use farming to you advantage that I have seen used on Xev is done by the 54 druid guild leader of a newbie guild. He farms EE bags out of Guk then sells them to the newbies in his guild for 200pp then gets them to resell them for 400pp each. They make money and he can move a much larger volume of the item and can basically corner the market on the item keeping the price very stable. I always give tells to members of the guild when I need an EE bag and I always get them for the 400pp they ask. This could be done with a larger number of items and when I was a new chanter on the block I needed that pp for my spells and some gear I was hoping for. Nice little trick.<br><br>I think in order to make an anology to RL the best way to compare trading it to think of yourself as a pawn broker. You are aquiring items from people who are in a hurry or have a need for something badly and you can sell it to them by having the patience they didn't. They extra money you make is for your time, not for the item itself. Are pawn shops looked down upon in RL? yes. Traders in EQ? yes. But who hasn't been happy with a great deal they got at a pawn shop at one time or another. <br><br>Also a good way to help your reputation is to sell items for a really good deal. Every now and then sell an item for what you bought it for just so people talk about the good deal you gave them. Or if they don't haggle just shave a bit off the price if you started the talks at a figure that was a bit high but you were expecting to haggle. Not everyone knows how to fight for a few plat but will remember when you take that 1k off that 20k item cause you like there spunk ;)<br><br>Good luck to you, trading is a fun way to improve your charecter without exping and give you something to do when all your friends are on vaction and you're bored of pick up groups full of goofs. Have fun get rich and give me a tell on Xev =) <br><br>Gedal Ogiona. If your not a Gnome your just fodder <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#778899><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub38.ezboard.com/usheanearrowless.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sheane Arrowless</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_ball.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Young Grasshoppah</span><br>  Posts: 10<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(10/27/01 6:27:50 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=565.topic&index=20>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Advanced trading.</span><hr size=1> Oh and one more note, if you sell at early morning times, most people wanna go to bed and sell their last thing, so i saw a barbed bp thingie, go from 15k to 9k back to 12k, don't ask <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :D --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/happy.gif ALT=":D"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> .<br>You can pick up lotsa cheap stuff in the mornings, but at about 6pm est or 8pm est its very hard to read all the auctions, everyone gets on, so thats when i start hunting again. Also be on the look out for cheap stuff, a charred guardian shield, one of the few items with less deflation, for only 200pp, go back the next day and sell for 500pp, voila easy 300pp <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> . <br><br>This is one method i used to get 1k on my monk with just a essence of dol and fighting baton, sold essence 400pp, saw cane for 300 bought it sold it for 900, saw someone buyin a fighting baton for 600 sold it, next day i got a fighting baton for 350pp and lateron a CoT for 300 again <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  so now i have those too and made some cash <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>Sounds easy eh? Well its not, its knowing the market value and knowing your items. <br>One thing of note, weapons seem to drop faster in price then armor, i mean the bonecaster robe has dropped 2k in price since i knew of that thing, but a CSS (12 24 good stats from seb) was 10k ish and now i see em for 4k !!! thats a drop of 6000pp!!!<br><br>And the same i can say for other weapons.<br><br>Good luck to you and drop me a tell on Lunatics, urmm i mean luclin <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><font color=green>Sheane Arrowless,</font><font color=Purple> Rangeres of Luclin</font><p><font color=gold>"Mess with the best, die like the rest" </font> <p><font color=purple>"All are equal in my eyes, its deeds that judge a man, not race."</font><font color=red>-Prince of Fire-(>''>)(>''<)(<''<)</font><p><font color=green><a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/bdisciplesofunderfoot>-Disciples of Underfoot-</a></font></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page  <b>1</b> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm2.showMessageRange?topicID=565.topic&start=21&stop=40>2</a><a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm2.showMessageRange?topicID=565.topic&start=41&stop=52>3</a> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm2.showNextMessage?topicID=565.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self hre